# Introduction

This document defines a technical profile for <protocol or system>. The profile
constrains the base specification and defines additional requirements for
deployments in a federation or similar multi-party environment.

## Terminology and Typographical Conventions

The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "REQUIRED", "SHALL", "SHALL NOT", "SHOULD",
"SHOULD NOT", "RECOMMENDED", "MAY", and "OPTIONAL" in this document are to be
interpreted as described in RFC2119 [@RFC2119].

Text in italics is non-normative. All other text is normative unless otherwise
stated.

## Terminology

The terminology from the base specification applies. The following additional
terms are used in this profile.

Member Organization
:    A federation member that is a legal entity and has one
or more entities registered in a federation.

Client
:    An entity that initiates a connection and authenticates to a
server using the authentication mechanism defined in the base specification.
